Conducting the T-Test

Lets conduct a t-test at 95% confidence level and see if it correctly rejects the null hypothesis that the sample comes from the same distribution as the employee population. To conduct a one sample t-test, we can use the stats.ttest_1samp() function:

## 
##  One Sample t-test
## 
## data:  left_pop$EmpSatisfaction
## t = -0.071654, df = 103, p-value = 0.943
## alternative hypothesis: true mean is not equal to 3.890675
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  3.716888 4.052342
## sample estimates:
## mean of x 
##  3.884615
